H0.text: Pseudocoelom is the partial body cavity filled with fluid in roundworms.

H1.text: The abdomen is the partial body cavity filled with fluid in roundworms.

H2.text: Cocklebur is a partial body cavity filled with fluid in roundworms.

H3.text: Spicule is the partial body cavity filled with fluid in roundworms.

A4.text: During copulation, one or more chitinized spicules move out of the cloaca and are inserted into the genital pore of the female.

A5.text: The abdominal cavity occupies the entire lower half of the trunk.

A6.text: Pseudocoelomate animals have a pseudocoelom which is a fluid filled body cavity.
